<p>Every exhibit follows the same rules.</p>
<p>The narrator never calls anyone a liar. When an accusation appears, it belongs to an institution with a paper trail: an IMF censure, a party disciplinary ruling, a statistics office correcting itself. I just do the arithmetic.</p>
<p>Every figure is checked against a primary source before it goes up, and the receipts sit at the bottom of each exhibit. Where the data is too dirty to chart honestly, the exhibit says so instead of drawing a line anyway. Sometimes the missing chart is the point.</p>
<p>Built openly with AI: Claude does the research sweeps, data pulls and first drafts. The editorial voice, the opinions, and any surviving errors are mine.</p>
<p>Every tenth exhibit, the site turns the method on itself: a meta-analysis of the collection so far, because a museum of discrepancies should be able to survive its own audit.</p>
